title: "tuple index out of range" when using Deep Explainer with PyTorch model
body:
I believe the line in question is this: https://github.com/slundberg/shap/blob/45b85c1837283fdaeed7440ec6365a886af4a333/shap/explainers/_deep/deep_pytorch.py#L58

this is my code:
```
# eval_feat_tensors is a list of 10 tensors, each one representing a feature
# in each tensor, there are 5 values, each representing a feature in that data record
# thus there are 5 records to learn from, with each record containing 10 features

e = shap.DeepExplainer(model, eval_feat_tensors)
shap_values = e.shap_values(eval_feat_tensors)
```
this produces the error `tuple index out of range`

my env:
```
shap v0.41.0
python v3.8.0
```

i believe the issue is that i output a tensor of 1D whereas the shap code expects a tensor of 2D - could someone tell me why it expects a tensor of 2D and if this is a feature request or a bug?

i believe the model works and outputs 10 prediction scores
```
model(*eval_feat_tensors)
=> tensor([ 0.4e-01, 5.4e-02, ...] grad_fn=<SelectBackward0>)

model(*eval_feat_tensors).shape
=> torch.Size([10])
```
